+12|S2 replaces the silent no-op for `defer` trigger actions with an explicit 
`TriggersError.unsupportedOperation('trigger-action.defer')` that routes the 
event to DLQ. The regression test proves this behavior and would catch a 
silent-drop regression. The reject decision is well-justified: `DeferAction` 
carries only `until: string` with no replay target or job payload, and no 
existing runtime path supports one-shot deferred dispatch. The cron scheduler 
handles recurring trigger definitions, and DLQ replay is a manual admin 
operation — neither provides one-shot action replay.
